                  </persName>
            . On Sunday about noon, the prisoner came to me, and said, he had lost all his money. We suspected the prisoner. Mrs. Allen told me, she had pawned the prosecutor's hat for a shilling. I told him, I thought he was a bad man to take ten or twelve guineas from the poor man; he said, No, it was but eight.</p>

